{"TopicId":162602,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"KSP and Siri question...","CreatedByName":"Spacetraindriver","CreatedById":149403,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-27T21:20:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spacetraindriver","CreatedById":149403,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-27T21:20:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst of all, mods, idk where to put this thread (Not gameplay related, Mac isn\u0027t PC :P) and its not exactly the most important question but if you have to then\u00A0move it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just found out Siri on my Mac can open all my games! The thing is, I can\u0027t play KSP. Well...Not exactly...I have to open it using the Unix executable due to something about OS X.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223219f752877cee639e2facf7daef2e3f.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://hostthenpost.org/uploads/3219f752877cee639e2facf7daef2e3f.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSiri only opens KSP (here)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bb2b708829c6df0a1b7206979f4444d5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://hostthenpost.org/uploads/bb2b708829c6df0a1b7206979f4444d5.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo does anyone know how to get Siri to directly execute the executable of KSP? Its not mandatory, I\u0027m just wondering if its possible...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-27T21:32:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe try creating a shortcut, and have her open that? Not on Mac, but i have an iPad...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-28T04:45:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot having it here in front of me I can only guess, but my first thought is that permissions are involved being KSP is likely viewed as a 3rd-party app.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-28T05:50:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry to speak reversed Spanish. Jeb would be happy talking to you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheRagingIrishman","CreatedById":165004,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-28T06:27:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149403-spacetraindriver/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149403\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149403-spacetraindriver/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Spacetraindriver\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0if you\u0027re installing from the ksp store, use the .pkg instead of the .zip for some reason the zip breaks the app\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-28T06:27:28Z\u0022 title=\u002206/28/2017 06:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 28, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by TheRagingIrishman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-29T02:33:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHas this been resolved \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149403-spacet